From: Jiri Pirko <jiri@resnulli.us>
Date: Fri, 6 Jun 2014 14:17:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 6/8] net: use SPEED_UNKNOWN and DUPLEX_UNKNOWN when
 appropriate
Patch-mainline: v3.16-rc1
Git-commit: 537fae0101c8853abb52136788173dde74b9d1e9 (partial)
References: bsc#922842 Fate#318524

Signed-off-by: Jiri Pirko <jiri@resnulli.us>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Acked-by: Cho, Yu-Chen <acho@suse.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/intel/igbvf/ethtool.c |    4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/igbvf/ethtool.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/igbvf/ethtool.c
@@ -101,8 +101,8 @@ static int igbvf_get_settings(struct net
 		else
 			ecmd->duplex = DUPLEX_HALF;
 	} else {
-		ethtool_cmd_speed_set(ecmd, -1);
-		ecmd->duplex = -1;
+		ethtool_cmd_speed_set(ecmd, SPEED_UNKNOWN);
+		ecmd->duplex = DUPLEX_UNKNOWN;
 	}
 
 	ecmd->autoneg = AUTONEG_DISABLE;
